    "Although the datasets are rich in types, originate from a vast range of sources, and have diverse modalities, they also have some issues with the actual training of the model.",
    "(1) The definition of negative samples was not standardized.",
    "Some current methods define a negative sample as one in which an unknown DTI relationship is directly trained as a negative sample, whereas in reality, drug-target relationships that are not excluded from wet experiments are likely to remain undetected simply due to hidden interactions.",
    "(2) The digital divide between positive and negative sample sizes.",
    "The small number of known DTIs relative to unknown drug-target relationships result in an extremely unbalanced dataset, which affects the effectiveness of the model training 20."
  ],
